%[text] # Skew and Two piece distributions
%[text] This toolbox contains several distributions to use complement those already shipping with statistics and machine learning toolbox. Namely:
%[text] - [SkewNormal](internal:H_C0F12C32) \[[Ref](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skew_normal_distribution)\]
%[text] - [SkewT](internal:H_D948BD53) \[[Ref](https://doi.org/10.1111/1467-9868.00391)\]
%[text] - [EpsilonSkewNormal](internal:H_A8752957) \[[Ref](https://doi.org/10.1016/S0378-3758(99)00096-8)\]
%[text] - [SplitNormal](internal:H_5BC740EC) \[[Ref](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Split_normal_distribution)\] \
%[text] First of all, to add all distributions to the MATLAB set, you need to run:
makedist -reset
%[text] After that, please use these distributions with any other function you would with any other from the shipping list. For example:
%[text] - [fitdsit](https://uk.mathworks.com/help/stats/fitdist.html?s_tid=doc_ta)
%[text] - [makedist](https://uk.mathworks.com/help/stats/makedist.html?s_tid=doc_ta) \
%%
%[text] %[text:anchor:H_C0F12C32] ## SkewNormal
%[text] PDF: $\\frac{2}{\\omega\\sqrt{2\\pi}}e^{-\\frac{(x-\\xi)^2}{2\\omega^2}} \\displaystyle\\int\_{-\\infty}^{\\alpha\\left(\\frac{x-\\xi}{\\omega}\\right)}{\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2\\pi}}e^{-\\frac{t^2}{2}}dt}$
pd = makedist('SkewNormal');
pd.alpha = 3;
pd.omega = 2;
pd.xi = 5;
data = pd.random(10000);
fitdist(data,'SkewNormal') %[output:5ed082f3]
histfit(data, 100, 'SkewNormal') %[output:09033a8c]
%%
%[text] %[text:anchor:H_D948BD53] ## SkewT
%[text] PDF: $2t\_{pdf}(z, \\nu)t\_{cdf}\\left(\\alpha \\frac{\\sqrt{1+\\nu}}{z^2+\\nu}, \\nu +1\\right) \\qquad where \\qquad z = \\frac{x-\\xi}{\\omega}$
pd = makedist('SkewT');
pd.xi = 2;
pd.omega = 0.5;
pd.alpha = 3;
pd.nu = 10;

data = pd.random(10000);
fitdist(data,'SkewT') %[output:9b67a0aa]
histfit(data, 100, 'SkewT') %[output:95df9c19]
%%
%[text] %[text:anchor:H_A8752957] ## EpsilonSkewNormal
%[text] PDF: $f\_X(x) = \\left\\{\\begin{array}{c}  \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{ 2 \\pi}}e^{\\frac{-x^2}{ 2(1 + \\epsilon)^2}}\\qquad x \< 0 \\\\  \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{ 2 \\pi}}e^{\\frac{-x^2}{ 2(1 - \\epsilon)^2}}  \\qquad x \\geq 0 \\end{array}\\right.$
pd = makedist('EpsilonSkewNormal');
pd.Theta = 2;
pd.Sigma = 3;
pd.Epsilon = 0.5;
data = pd.random(10000,1);
fitdist(data,'EpsilonSkewNormal') %[output:0d98452d]
histfit(data, 100, 'EpsilonSkewNormal') %[output:91370a04]
%%
%[text] %[text:anchor:H_5BC740EC] ## SplitNormal
%[text] PDF: $f\_X(x) = \\left\\{\\begin{array}{c} \\frac{\\sqrt{2/\\pi}}{\\sigma\_1+\\sigma\_2}\\exp\\left(-\\frac{(x-\\mu)^2}{2\\sigma\_1^2}\\right) \\qquad x \< \\mu \\\\ \\frac{\\sqrt{2/\\pi}}{\\sigma\_1+\\sigma\_2}\\exp\\left(-\\frac{(x-\\mu)^2}{2\\sigma\_2^2}\\right) \\qquad x \\geq \\mu \\end{array}\\right.$
pd = makedist('SplitNormal');
pd.sigma1 = 1;
pd.sigma2 = 5;
pd.mu = 4;
data = pd.random(10000);
fitdist(data,'SplitNormal') %[output:6305061c]
histfit(data, 100, 'SplitNormal') %[output:1088e4b2]

